Navigate to other release versions of Doxee Platform Business Designer

[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/business-designer-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/business-designer-6-7)

If versioning is activated in the repository, the versioning icon is displayed in the title bar of open files. Clicking on the icon opens a menu with these options:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

***Enable versioning***: enables versioning, creates the first version v1.0 and the file is immediately opened in read only mode. The file is now checked in.

***Checkout***: Is available as soon as versioning is enabled. If a file is checked out, it is locked to other users. They only have the option of viewing this file in read only mode and cannot save any changes in this file. If the user wants to make changes anyway, the file can be saved as a new file (Save As). Users are notified of the checked out status when they open the file. If changes are to be made to a file, it is advisable to first check out this file.

If the file is checked out and opened, the versioning icon changes - it is now shown with an arrow pointing to the top right.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Checked out files are displayed in the file picker window with a blue dot on the template icon:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

***Checkin***: Is available as soon as the file has been checked out by the same user. *Checkin *checks in the file and creates a new version (increase the version from e.g. v1.0 to v1.1). You can set a comment for each version which will be shown in the version history dialog. You can also leave the comment field empty.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The file is reloaded after each check-in and a dialog appears in which the user can choose whether they want to check out the file or open it in read only mode:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Checked-in files are also displayed in the file picker window with a blue dot on the template icon.

The versioning icon changes for checked-in files - it is shown with an arrow pointing downwards:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

***Discard Checkout***: is available as soon as the file has been checked out and edited by the same user. Checkout will be reversed and all changes since the last checkout will be discarded. Corresponds to discarding all changes without saving, i.e. it jumps back to the last checked-in version.

***Version History***: is available as soon as the versioning of the file has been activated. All versions of the file are available in the opened dialog. Older versions are opened in read only mode by double-clicking and the version information is displayed on the opened tab. By single click the version is marked and the comment of the version is shown in the lower area. In this example the comment is "all done!". Additionally, there is an option on this dialog to

show or hide indirect versions (bottom left). Indirect versions occur when there are multiple versions of a referenced file. For example, it may happen that the main file is checked in and version 1.4 is created. After version 1.4 of the main file was created (shown in blue), referenced files can be edited and multiple versions of that referenced file can be created (gray version number). Thus there are several timestamps with different versions. The possibility to open the main file 1.4 with all indirect versions exists, in this example the versions 1.2, 1.3 and 1.4, the indirect versions can be shown. The files from a certain timestamp can be opened by double click.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Another way of displaying the history is the timeline (selection at the top center):

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
